rComments: Amazing and fun course. Prof. makes the course extremely fun with jokes and real world examples. It is very hard to get above 80 and below 73 in this course. If you take great lecture notes and read his handouts you should be good.

rComments: One of the best professors i met in UTM. I love his lecture, he is a very humorous guy. I really hope he could teach MGT421, not PT, the most arrogant and annoying guy in commerce department.
he's one of the best profs in UTM he will help you and he's easy to approach i've has him for 321 and 393 and he explains everything in great detail
Best prof i had in my 3 years, knows exactly what he is talking about.

rComments: Professor Schneider truly cares about his students.  Wish more instructors had his level of dedication and commitment.   Well liked by all students.

He is in charge of breaking the Business Law from a full year course before to now two half year courses (393 and 394). Really simplified 393 a lot and provided clear examples to demonstrate the law. His tests have no surprises but not easy. Overall good course and wonderful instructor.
Prof Schneider is one of the best lecturers at UTM. He provides lots of examples to make the sometimes dry material more interesting and holds your attention with occasional jokes.
Best Prof and he loves Taylor Swift, every tests he had her name on the paper and sent us email about some Taylor Swift's latest songs. but still best prof ever

Best professor I've had in my entire life.  Extremely caring, very fair, down to earth & professional.  You won't meet many people like this in your life.  I graduated 7 years ago from UTM and the only professor I always admire is Prof. Schneider.  I still remember his lectures in business law & auditing.  He teaches with his full heart, I believe.
Amazing prof! Didn't use the textbook for this class, just went to lectures and studied his notes. His teaching style is very refreshing and you can tell he cares a lot about his students.

He is the best professor in the entire UTM Management Department. He explains with examples & uses humour to make sure the class remembers the material. I wish he taught me all my accounting courses! Understand the material & practice as many cases as possible then get feedback! You will do great! BEST BEST PROFESSOR EVER!

In the classes I took with Schneider, before the final, my mark would be in the B's. After the exam, my mark jumps to A's. That is because after I do bad on midterms, I go to his office hours where he gives you the BEST TIPS. Apply  his tips on the exam and you'll do well. Funniest Prof I've had!
Amazing professor. Explains examples with great sense of humor and current life events so its easy to remember. Actually makes you think twice about attending law school.
Very nice professor. Go to his class and listen to his lectures and youre done.All he wants you to do is use his words in the exam and youll do great.

I loved his teaching style. He uses stories and his sense of humour to make you remember. You'll understand the concept if you focus and listen. However, it's pretty hard to get an A. It's one of those "lets give most students a B" course.
Not great-seems nice until the evaluations are done--then he burns you on the final.
this course is my gpa killer. i tried hard but the mark was so heart-breaking. the prof is very nice.

Great Prof. One of the smartest people you will ever meet. He has a great teaching style and never has to refer to any notes since it is all in his head. It's not hard to get above 70% in his classes but getting above 80% can be a challenge.
Chilly Pepper? You got to be kidding.....
Amazing prof.... not the easiest course in the world but the coolest teacher .... he is really down to earth.

He is one of the best profs at UTM and definitely the best Commerce prof.  He has a unique style of teaching but it helps you understand the material.  He is enthusiastic about what he teaches and it seems that he cares about the students.  However, his TAs are hard markers - if you don't answer the question asked, you will not get a good grade.
AWESOME TEACHER!
